# Signal-to-Action Agent POC Rules

- Follow `signal-agent-poc/INSTRUCTIONS.md` and `signal-agent-poc/ARCHITECTURE.md` as source of truth.
- Keep read and write operations separated.
- Read-only skills (`ingest_transcript`, `detect_painpoint`, `lookup_account`, `evaluate_intent`, `lookup_specialist`) must not write files or send messages.
- Only `skills/notify.py` may append to `data/output/signal_log.jsonl`.
- Never contact customers. Internal notifications only.
- Start routing as console output only.
- Do not call Webex, Outlook, Salesforce, Gong, Cisco, Hasura, or any unexposed enterprise endpoint.
- Keep OpenAI optional and the deterministic fallback required.
- Never hard-code secrets. Do not print API key values or partial key values.
- Keep each skill small and single-purpose.
- Every run must log a JSONL record, including NOISE runs.
- Demonstrate both HIGH_INTENT and NOISE behavior when validating changes.
